Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of dense connections in the proposed network, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under the domain of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the efficiency and accuracy of the proposed method, which involves optimization and evaluation techniques, respectively. Therefore, cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for tiny object detection, which involves the use of deep learning and optimization techniques. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category.
